Class Edge<G extends IGraph<G,E,N>,E extends IEdge<G,E,N>,N extends INode<G,E,N>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uniol.apt.adt.extension.Extensible
      • uniol.apt.adt.Edge<G,E,N>
  • Type Parameters:
    G - the graph the edge belongs to.
    E - the edge class itself.
    N - the node class belonging to the graph.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IExtensible, IEdge<G,E,N>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Arc, Flow

    public class Edge<G extends IGraph<G,E,N>,E extends IEdge<G,E,N>,N extends INode<G,E,N>>
extends Extensible
implements IEdge<G,E,N>
    Represents an edge of type E in a graph of type G with nodes of type N having a id of the source node and target node.
    Author:
    Dennis-Michael Borde, Manuel Gieseking
